The Guild of Opportunity<br>
<br>
1. Raids<br>
<br>
A. Distibution of Loot<br>
<br>
I) If an item is dropped that is wanted by only one person, that needs that item, then they shall be allowed to loot that item<br>
<br>
II) If an item is dropped that wanted by only one person, that does not need that item, then they shall be allowed to loot that item. However, they are required to keep said item for at least one week, in case there is another guild member who needs that item. If a week passes without such a case, then the looter shall be allowed to do as they wish with said item.<br>
<br>
III) If an item is dropped that is wanted by more than one person, and only one out of the amount needs it, that one person shall get the item in favor of those that have no need for it.<br>
<br>
IV) If an item is dropped that is wanted by more than one person, and all or a few need it, it shall be rolled for to determine who gets the rights to loot it.<br>
<br>
V) If an item is dropped thatis wanted by more than one person, and none of them need it, it shall be rolled for and given to the winner. However, they are required to keep said item for at least one week, in case there is another guild member who needs that item. If a week passes without such a case, then the looter shall be allowed to as they wish with said item.<br>
<br>
B. Definitions<br>
<br>
I) Want – If a person expresses an interest in looting an item dropped by a mob, then they are said to “want” that item. If a person needs an item, but expresses no interest in that item, then they do not want that item, and should not be considered to be trying for that item.<br>
<br>
II) Need – If a person directly benefits from possesing an item dropped by a mob, rhen they are said to “need” that item. Selling an item for money is not considered a direct need. A person need not gain statistics from an item, but if two people need an item, the person with the greatest benefits from the item will usually get the itemm. If the difference in gained benefit is small, then rollngi  will occur as usual.<br>
<br>
C. Planning<br>
<br>
I) Initiation – Any member of the guild may propose a raid, may orginize a raid, and may run a raid, barring the permission of guild leaders for leading. However, no guild member may orginize a raid on a newbie-friendly zone, such as a city with trading NPCs, .and should avoid killing quest initators.<br>
<br>
II)  Time – Raids may take place at any time of the day, for as long as is needed. If a raid iterferes with another guild’s raid, then the raid shall be postponed until such a time that the scheduling of the raid does not interfere.<br>
<br>
III) Members – Any member of the guild may participate in any raid. Preferably, raid members will be in the correct level range for the place being raided, but younger observers and older helpers are certainly allowed as well. Members of other guild, and non-guilded people, will be allowed, barring interview by the raid orginizerm,and after being explained the rules for raided that have been set forth by the guild.<br>
<br>
D. Raid Offenses<br>
<br>
I) Intentional Training – If a person purposefully trains a group of aggressive mobs onto a raiding party, whether that is for the purpose of killing the raid members or making them evac, that is known as Intentional Training. Normal training happens all the time, purely by accident, so it must be proven beyond doubt that the training was intentional for there to be an offence. If the trainer was a member of the guild, they will be given a warning, and be suspended from raids and other guild activities (besides meetings) for a month. If they choose not to comply with the sentence, they shall be banned from the guild and all guild activities, barring any future amnisty. If the trainer is not a member of the guild, they will be banned from the guild and their guild will be informed of their actions.<br>
<br>
II) Loot Stealing – If a person purposefully takes an item from a slain mob that has been promised to another person, that is known as Loot Stealing. If the stealer is a member of the guild, then they will be asked once nicely by the leader of the raid to give the item to the person who was to receive it in the first place. If they fail to comply, then they shall receive a warning and shall be banned from all guild activities (besides meetings) for a month. If they still fail to comply, they shall be gbanned from the guild and all guild activities. If the stealer is not from the guild, they will be asked once nicely by the leader of the raid to give the item to the person who was to receive it in the first place. If they fail to comply, then they shall be banned from guild activities and their guild shall be informed of their actions.<br>
<br>
III) Other – All other offences shall eb determned later<br>
<br>
2. Guild regulations<br>
<br>
A. Channels<br>
<br>
I) Say/Tells – Guild members may use the say channel how they see fit, barring the rules for all channel behavior.<br>
<br>
II) Auction – Guild members may use the auction channel how they see fit, barring the rules for all channel behavior. It would be prefered that guild members leave seeling to the Bazaar, but if that’s not an option, or if you are traveling and wish to seel, oit won’t be a problem.<br>
<br>
III) Group – If a guild member is in a group with other guild members, they are allowed to use the public guild channel to coordinate if they wish, although they should hold down on the chatter about the group to a minimum to lessen channel spam. If a guild member is in a group with members outside the guild, they should use the guild channel to coordinate events.<br>
<br>
IV) Shout – Guild members should keep use of the shout channel to a minimum. If a member does not have the Legends of Ykesha expansion, they may use it to advertize looking for a group. Auctioning items should be left to the appropriate channel, and non-local interguild contacts should be left to tells and the guild channel.<br>
<br>
V) Opportunty/Guild – The Opportunty chat channel, for current purposes, serves as a guild channel would. In the future, the Opportunity channel will remain open as a channel for potential applicants to meet guild members. The guild chat will become the interguild chat channel.<br>
<br>
B. Chat Rules<br>
<br>
I) Language – Any language may be spoken by guild members, but any member that joins the guild should make it a point to try to learn human. This will make communication at meetings and such easier for all sides. This does not mean that other languages are not allowed, or that not knowing human is grounds for any sort of punishment<br>
<br>
II) Roleplaying – Roleplaying is highly encouraged in the guild, and all opportunities to remain that are presented should be taken. That said, it is understood that sometimes things must be said out of character, or that someone might not feel like they are up to roleplaying at a given moment. These will be rspected, and there shall nbe no punishment of any sort for going out of character. Still, people should try to label being out of character if in the middle of a roleplaying enviorment.<br>
<br>
III) Swearing – Swearing in guild chat or without allowance with a person is highly frowned upon by the guild. We are all adults, but we must respect each other. While swearing is not inherently punishable, excessive swearing will be dealt with. If asked to stop swearing, and a person fails to comply, they will be given a warning and be suspended form guild events (exceopting meetings) for a month. If they still choose to ignore the rule, then they shall be banned from the guild and all guild activities.<br>
<br>
IV) Harassment – All forms of verbal harassment, from religious to sexual, and including racial and ageism, is not allowed in the guild. If a member is caught engaging in language that is of a harrasing nature, they shall immediately be givene a warning, and be suspended for guild events for 30 days. If they persist,, they shall be banned from the guild and guild activities. If a person wishes to roeplay such a thing, they must get explicet concent from their fellow roleplayer. We take this very seriously!<br>
